## Layout

```
{{ project_slug }}/
├── backend/    # Litestar API (uv)
├── frontend/   # SvelteKit app (bun)
├── deploy/     # nginx config
├── compose.yaml
├── justfile     # task runner
└── Makefile     # same tasks for `make` users
```

> Every `just <task>` below has an identical `make <task>` target — use whichever you prefer.

## Getting started

A git-ignored `.env` was generated with your answers — review it first.

### Dockerized (everything in containers)

```bash
just dev        # postgres + api (reload) + web (dev) via docker compose
```

The web dev server is published on `http://localhost:{{ frontend_port }}`. The first
`just dev`/`just up` is slow because it runs `bun install` in the container — wait for the
`VITE ... ready` line (`docker compose logs -f web`) before opening the page.

### Local (run api + web on your machine)

Runs the backend and frontend directly on your host against a dockerized Postgres. The
`.env` `DATABASE_URL` already points at `{{ db_host }}:{{ db_port }}`, and Vite proxies
`/api` to the local backend.

```bash
just bootstrap  # uv sync + bun install (once)
just db         # start only Postgres in docker
just be-upgrade # apply migrations to the local db (once, and after new migrations)
just be-run     # backend  -> http://localhost:{{ backend_port }}
just fe-run     # frontend -> http://localhost:{{ frontend_port }}  (in a second terminal)
```

Prefer a local Postgres over docker? Set `DATABASE_URL` in `.env` to point at it and skip
`just db`.

